AN
INVESTIGATION
OF
OPTIMUM
ZOOM
CLIMB
TECHNIQUES
THE
PROBLEM
OF
OPTIMAL
ZOOM
CLIMB
MANEUVERING
OF
A
TURBOJET
AIRCRAFT
HAS
BEEN
INVESTIGATED
USING
THE
MAYER
FORMULATION
OF
THE
CALCULUS
OF
VARIATIONS
THE
EULERLAGRANGE
EQUATIONS
GOVERNING
OPTIMUM
SYMMETRIC
FLIGHT
HAVE
BEEN
INTEGRATED
NUMERICALLY
BY
DIGITAL
COMPUTATION
DISCONTINUITIES
IN
THRUST
ARISING
FROM
TURBOJET
AFTERBURNER
BLOWOUT
HAVE
BEEN
TREATED
AND
CONDITIONS
WHICH
MUST
BE
SATISFIED
ACROSS
THE
INTERFACE
GENERATED
BY
THE
DISCONTINUITY
HAVE
BEEN
DERIVED
ARBITRARY
CONTROL
TECHNIQUES
HAVE
BEEN
COMPARED
WITH
THE
OPTIMUM
AND
IT
HAS
BEEN
FOUND
THAT
PERFORMANCE
IS
RELATIVELY
INSENSITIVE
TO
PILOTING
TECHNIQUE
UNLESS
A
TIME
LIMITATION
IS
IMPOSED
WHICH
REQUIRES
HIGH
MANEUVERING
LOAD
FACTORS
